OL,3,CInside Haiti's humanitarian emergency
OL,4,Cwhere gang violence rules the streets
OL,6,FThese are places that news
OL,7,Forganisations have difficulty getting
OL,8,Faccess to.
OL,10,FWhile I'm there, I try to focus on
OL,11,Flistening to people who are trapped,
OL,12,Fstruggling to feed their families, on
OL,13,Fthat razor-thin line between hunger
OL,14,Fand starvation. I try to give a voice
OL,15,Fto the forgotten hungry.
OL,17,FI've been to Haiti several times in
OL,18,Fthe past few years as violent armed
OL,19,Fgroups have steadily increased their
OL,20,Fcontrol over the capital and spread
OL,21,Fthroughout the country.
