OL,3,CInside Haiti's humanitarian emergency
OL,4,Cwhere gang violence rules the streets
OL,6,FCurrently, 90% of Haiti's besieged
OL,7,Fcapital, Port-au-Prince, is under
OL,8,Ftheir control. This tightening noose
OL,9,Fhas been strangling trade, transport,
OL,10,Fand importation of essential fuel,
OL,11,Ffood supplies, and humanitarian aid.
OL,13,FTravel to the capital by road is
OL,14,Fincreasingly dangerous due to
OL,15,Fcheckpoints and roadblocks set up by
OL,16,Farmed groups and vigilante
OL,17,Fneighbourhood defence committees.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/19
