OL,3,CInside Haiti's humanitarian emergency
OL,4,Cwhere gang violence rules the streets
OL,6,FFarmers in rural areas are being
OL,7,Fkidnapped, raped, and murdered. They
OL,8,Foften have to pay bribes to get their
OL,9,Fproduce to the capital, so food in
OL,10,FPort au Prince is prohibitively
OL,11,Fexpensive ` a factor which led to the
OL,12,Fonly famine-like levels of hunger ever
OL,13,Frecorded in the western hemisphere.
OL,15,FLast year, several commercial
OL,16,Fairliners were shot at while landing,
OL,17,Fand the US aviation authority
OL,18,Fsubsequently banned US aircraft from
OL,19,Fflying to the country's main airport
OL,20,Fin Port-au-Prince.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/19
