OL,3,CInside Haiti's humanitarian emergency
OL,4,Cwhere gang violence rules the streets
OL,6,FSince then, flights to the capital
OL,7,Fhave been few and far between. The
OL,8,Fonly commercial airline flying between
OL,9,Fthe US to anywhere in Haiti uses
OL,10,Foperators the US Government hires to
OL,11,Foperate deportation flights from the
OL,12,FUS to Latin America.
OL,14,FCurrently, the only safe way for
OL,15,Fhumanitarians and diplomats to access
OL,16,Fthe capital is by a helicopter, which
OL,17,Fis operated by the WFP-run United
OL,18,FNations Humanitarian Air Service
OL,19,F(UNHAS).
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/19
