OL,3,CInside Haiti's humanitarian emergency
OL,4,Cwhere gang violence rules the streets
OL,6,FSeveral weeks ago, I ran the gauntlet
OL,7,Ffrom the port city of Cap Hatien to
OL,8,FPort-au-Prince in an UNHAS Sikorsky
OL,9,Ffilled with aid workers. We flew low
OL,10,Fthrough mist-covered hills and over
OL,11,Fformer plantations where most of the
OL,12,Fworld's sugar and coffee supply once
OL,13,Fcame from.
OL,15,FWe landed near the WFP's office on a
OL,16,Fhill southeast of the city centre.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/19
