OL,3,CInside Haiti's humanitarian emergency
OL,4,Cwhere gang violence rules the streets
OL,6,FSeparated from their livelihoods with
OL,7,Fno income to buy food with, it is
OL,8,Fplaces like these where displaced
OL,9,Fpeople are staying, where WFP is
OL,10,Fseeing cases of severe malnutrition,
OL,11,Fand the risk of famine is most
OL,12,Fconcerning.
OL,14,FIn this school, I met Rose, who was
OL,15,Fcradling her 18-month-old
OL,16,Fgranddaughter, Nelaika, at a WFP-
OL,17,Fsupported mobile clinic.
