OL,3,CInside Haiti's humanitarian emergency
OL,4,Cwhere gang violence rules the streets
OL,6,FHere, armed groups have carved out
OL,7,Ftheir fiefdoms, constructing walls
OL,8,Fusing cinderblocks as if they were the
OL,9,Ffortifications of medieval villages.
OL,11,FThe only reason we were able to get
OL,12,Fthis far into Cite Soliel was thanks
OL,13,Fto a very skilled WFP team armed with
OL,14,Fthe gift of persuasion.
OL,16,FWFP access teams are capable of
OL,17,Fconvincing some of the world's most
OL,18,Fdangerous warlords, militias, or
OL,19,Fcriminal groups to allow WFP to bring
OL,20,Flifesaving aid to people living in
OL,21,Ftheir territory.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G13/19
