OL,3,CInside Haiti's humanitarian emergency
OL,4,Cwhere gang violence rules the streets
OL,6,FResidents, caught up in the violence
OL,7,Fgripping the city, peered nervously at
OL,8,Fus out of their thatched huts. But in
OL,9,Fthe midst of this seemingly tense
OL,10,Fscene, slivers of hope are emerging.
OL,12,FYears of collapsed infrastructure had
OL,13,Fresulted in silt blocking the
OL,14,Firrigation canals that fed this
OL,15,Fpotentially productive area. To
OL,16,Fharvest bananas and other food crops,
OL,17,Fpeople had to journey deep into the
OL,18,Fforest.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G15/19
