OL,3,CInside Haiti's humanitarian emergency
OL,4,Cwhere gang violence rules the streets
OL,6,FThanks to WFP's access team in Haiti,
OL,7,FAugustine and his colleagues were
OL,8,Fallowing WFP to hire people who
OL,9,Fremained in the community to
OL,10,Frehabilitate the irrigation system and
OL,11,Fgrow desperately needed food closer to
OL,12,Ftheir homes.
OL,14,FI asked Augustine why they agreed to
OL,15,Fthe WFP-supported project in their
OL,16,Fterritory. He shrugged and said: "We
OL,17,Fagreed because people here are hungry
OL,18,Fand we want them (WFP) to come and
OL,19,Fhelp the community."
