OL,6,F"Toutotan tet ou poko koupe, espere
OL,7,Fmet chapo" is a Haitian phrase used to
OL,8,Fgive hope when all seems hopeless. It
OL,9,Fbanally translates to mean "as long as
OL,10,Fyou haven't had your head cut off,
OL,11,Fthere is hope that you can wear a hat."
OL,13,FThere is hope for Haiti, and Felix
OL,14,Fshould be wearing a crown.
